            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1726.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Run the <strong>drained potatoes </strong>under the cold tap until cool enough to handle</p>\n<p>Return them to the pot and crush gently</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> cooked smoked basa </strong>with the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix gently</p>\n<p>Divide the mix into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span>, then shape them into<strong> fish cakes</strong> by squeezing together and finally coat them in <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1726.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
